Class FunctionExpression<O,R>

  • java.lang.Object

  • Type Parameters:
    O - The type of the operand.
    R - The type of the result.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Expression<R>, MutableExpression<R>, Observable<Expression<R>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Negation, NOT

    public class FunctionExpression<O,R>
extends DependentExpression<R>
    An implementation of Expression with a single data dependency, whose value is derived through the application of a function to the value of that dependency. This function may also be provided through an Expression dependency.
